rComments: Probably the worst professor I've had in my 4 years at the university. Could not understand a word he was saying. He would never answer students' questions directly. Would just read off his slides and so many mistakes on his slides. No textbook, so very difficult to actually learn. Not sure why this prof teaches at a university level.

The class average was a 30 for social context of business which is inconceivable considering it's one of the easiest classes at Telfer, avoid if you actually want a fair mark! He doesn't have a textbook but his slides are clearly google translated because they're filled with grammatical errors.
The final was extremely unfair and lectures were disorganized. He was mostly late, and unprofessional during office hours: avoid at all costs!

Very nice guy for sure. But everybody knows it, he's a bad professor, nothing much we can do about that. If you're forced to take a course with him, just study by yourself, you'll be better off. Good luck!

Learn the powerpoints and you'll be fine. Not very useful to go to class, and the stuff he gives to read is not useful unless you have time to waste. He expects more than he ask in the exams even when faced when the fact that the question doesn't ask for more.
Very bad teacher. I barely learnt a thing in this class. I missed out on a potentially enriching and enjoyable class because he taught it.

I wish he could show a little bit more respect to students, after we are paying customers to the University of Ottawa and it baffles me why they'd pick someone like him to "teach" He doesn't have office hours, and doesn't care about his students!
Is very rude and disrespectful when you ask for extra help, very glad to be finished with this "professor"

Friendly demeanor but overall terrible experience. Reads off PowerPoints - lots of theory, little to no application. Group project was cancelled and brought back - little instruction. Midterm doable but final was impossible - it contained content not taught or expected details for topics he briefly skimmed. Does not explain well - goes in circles.

He's the worst teacher I have ever had!! His final exam is literally impossible and makes no absolute sense (not specific at all and very vague). I was glad I passed the class after the struggle I had even going through it. If possible, DON'T TAKE THIS CLASS!!! This is the biggest warning I've ever given in school.
Avoid this prof if possible. If not take it in English. He reads his powerpoints and puts no effort in teaching.  Midterm was doable but the final made no sense!
TERRIBLE!

As a straight A student, I can honestly tell you this is the hardest class I have ever had and just hoped to pass. The midterm was ok with random multiple choice questions but once we got to the final nothing made sense. No textbook, slides suck, useless lectures. Most people failed. Avoid at all costs!

Worst prof I have ever had, the final is impossible and I don't know anyone who passed! He is a hard grader and does not know how to teach a class and when you go see him to review your grade, he won't add you any points even if you prove that your answer was right! Do not take him is you want to pass!

Worst prof ever. No textbook. I tried to argue my grade and he practically laughed in my face. He's very stubborn, talks in circles, does not explain anything properly and only reads his powerpoints. I'm a A/B+ student and I failed his class. I would not recommend him to anyone EVER! AVOID AT ALL COSTS!!
He is the worst prof !!!! Every one I know including myself failed the class!! Avoid him if you want to pass
WORST PROF EVER!!! AVOID HIM!!!!! FINAL EXAM IS IMPOSSIBLE AND THIS IS COMING FROM A STRAIGHT A STUDENT!!!

He didn't give any instructions or format to follow when it came to the group project but still graded it toughly. Midterm was a joke (had multiple choice and True/False) but final only consisted of written questions. Powerpoints filled with mistakes and no examples given in class. Went into the final with an A- and finished with a C+. Awful prof

En lisant les commentaires des etudiants, il me semble utile d'ajouter le mien. Je n'ai rien appris de ce prof.  L'examen final est une moquerie des gens; il ne test rien mais Il te met dans une situation d'echec presque sure. Ses notes de cours sont pourris. Sa communication est horrible. Il est la juste pour gagner un salaire. Eviter ce prof !

This man has very serious communication and behavioural problems. His final exam is just impossible. I am pretty sure he  made that complex for his own Ego! This is really sick!. His classes are so weak and boring. He does nothing to inspire the 1st year students. He is not a nice man; he is not a leader; He is not a Teacher, period. Please avoid

In all honesty, this is not a "PROFESSOR" per se: (1) Very bad communicator in Listening & Speaking. (2) Arrogant towards nice (or weak) students; (3) Does not care if you understood his "awful" material. It is a "shame" for OttawaU to hire such an "academic" staff to inspire future business men and women of Canada !! Strongly avoid this "teacher"

AVOID at all costs. Terrible prof. Initially gave almost everyone a D+ or lower but had to increase everyone's grades after the school investigated. Had a typo in every email/slide and changed our course outline multiple times. Avoid, avoid, avoid.

The midterm was extremely easy and walking  to the final exam I had a 83.5%. The exam was EXTREMELY HARD FOR NO REASON. There was 2 questions I couldn't respond because it was "des sujets de discussion discuté en classe". For someone that was in every single class he didn't mention any of that. AVOID HIM OR IF YOU CANT DON'T SKIP CLASS!

The absolute WORST professor at the University. The final was ludicrously unfair, with unseen content from either the textbook or course comprising of 80% of the exam. Going into the exam with a A-, imagine my surprise leaving with a unmoving C+. Along with both cancelling and bringing back the Final Project DAYS before its due, avoid at all costs.

Terrible teacher. Reads his powerpoints, extremely boring course content and lectures. His midterm is quite easy but his exam was extremely hard... very specific questions and we had 200 slides to study for. Lots of definitions on the exam, no exam review. No textbook therefore you need to use his powerpoints to study which are filled with mistakes

Avoid this teacher if possible. He comes to class only to read the powerpoints, his midterm is not bad but he makes the final impossible and he gives everyone a bad grade for the group project (everyone I talked to got less than 65%).

I thought I was doing fairly okay, but he doesn't explain a whole lot and absolutely no one was prepared for the final. You have no idea what to expect going into the final because the midterm was a joke and we hadn't gotten our group project back. The lack of a textbook makes it impossible to supplement what he's teaching.

Most boring class I've ever been in! Not only his powerpoints filled with mistakes, they don't relate to what he actually teaches in class. His midterm is not that bad but his final is deadly and barely covered what was actually on the powerpoints. There's no book for the class so you can't even teach youself. AVOID THIS TEACHERR!!
The exams are hard and during his lectures he would read the powerpoints.. so it was useless to attend

Honestly put no effort at all into making the material interesting, wouldn't even classify him as a prof, all he does is read the power points that he posts online anyways. No point in going to class, wouldn't recommend because he makes his final ridiculously hard for no reason, on material you didn't even learn in class. Terrible terrible.

En tant que tel is his favorite saying but like does he even know what it means ?  He basically repeats whats on his powerpoints, his lectures are miserable, he puts 0 effort. He also makes the midterm a jokke but the final impossible  but no text book .. goodluck

Everyone I spoke to received the same percentage grade for an assignment worth 50%. Based on that I don't think he's really putting much effort into the course. He's a very good presenter.  He graded the final extremely harshly - most people were done in 30 - 45 minutes (for a 3hr exam), but no one I spoke to received over 75%. Senseless.

This man says he's an intelligent person and evenr writes  Dr. before his name.... I honestly think he should go see a doctor because  he suffers from HyperStupidity + short and long term memory loss.   Wich means, while preparing an exam he totally forgets what he teached in class.. So exams have nothing to do with what you guys are studying
Very hard final exam, friendly prof.
